def: To gather into a ball; to collect into a round mass.Then founded, then conglobed Like things to like. Milton.
An orthographic projection, sometimes partly in section, esp.of a building.

Entitled to worship, reverence, or high respect; claimingrespect; worthy of honor; -- often used as a term of respect,sometimes ironically. "This is worshipful society." Shak.[She is] so dear and worshipful. Chaucer.-- Wor"ship*ful*ly, adv.-- Wor"ship*ful*ness, n.
Western Christians of the Latin rite. See Orientals. Shipley.
A short stick, with one end loaded, or thicker and heavier thatthe other, used as an offensive weapon.
The quality or state of being slovenly.
A fine kind of leather, prepared commonly from goatskin (thoughan inferior kind is made of sheepskin), and tanned with sumac anddyed of various colors; -- said to have been first made by the Moors.
A kind of helmet. [Written also burganet.] Shak.
